    @Entity
    @Table(name = &quot;node&quot;)
    @AllArgsConstructor
    @NoArgsConstructor
    @Getter
    @Setter
    @JsonNaming(PropertyNamingStrategies.SnakeCaseStrategy.class) 
    public class Node {
        @EmbeddedId
        private NodeIdentifier nodeIdentifier;
        private Long nodePosition;
    
        @ManyToMany(mappedBy = &quot;nodes&quot;)
        private List&lt;Tree&gt; trees;
    }

In the `Tree` class, a `@ManyToMany` annotation to define the many-to-many relationship with the `Node` class. Specified the `@JoinTable` annotation to define the join table name and the join columns that link the `Tree` entity to the join table. The `inverseJoinColumns` attribute specifies the join columns that link the `Node` entity to the join table.

In the `Node` class, a `@ManyToMany` annotation with the `mappedBy` attribute, which tells `JPA` that the `nodes` field is the inverse side of the relationship and that the owning side is the `Tree` entity. This avoids creating a separate join entity to represent the many-to-many association.

