    public class TreeNodeId implements Serializable {
        private String treeId;
        private String nodeId;
        
        @Override
        public int hashCode() {
            return Objects.hash(treeId, nodeId);
        }
        
        @Override
        public boolean equals(Object obj) {
            if (this == obj)
                return true;
            if (obj == null || getClass() != obj.getClass())
                return false;
            TreeNodeId that = (TreeNodeId) obj;
            return Objects.equals(treeId, that.treeId) &amp;&amp; Objects.equals(nodeId, that.nodeId);
        }
    }

`TreeNode` has a composite primary key `TreeNodeId` that consists of the primary keys of both `Tree` and `Node` entities. The `tree` and `node` associations are mapped using `@MapsId`, which tells `JPA` to use the same primary key as the `TreeNodeId`

